<L>__{interior eddie's building stairwell dusk}
<A>__{it's a former tenement, fourth floor walk up. eddie trudges up the old stairs, the tiny tiles worn away in spots, the victorian moldings disfigured from a hundred and twenty years of painterior eddie is suddenly seized by a racking cough a horrible smoker's cough that makes him double over. he sounds like he's 80 years old. he finally gets it under control, gets a glimpse of himself in the storefront window. he looks bad, and he knows he looks bad. he reaches into his pocket. the pill sits teasingly in the palm of his hand, looking up at him.}
<C>__{eddie }
<D>__{well. there was less than nothing to lose.}
<A>__{quickly, impulsively, he swallows it.}
